Heath, evening

Thanks for making the changes, further details to be changed

If you could please have your team check through all details carefully as I am spending time finding things they are missing on each occasion and they have added errors which weren't there previously.

  • Question - Do you have a spouse/partner?

  • For the income cell please force it to be a number with a $ mark just like the insurance calculator, see below

Example of how the insurance calculator forces a number and adds in the $ sign

**** Please force this on every cell that requires a number entry just like the insurance calculator

  • Question - Do you own your own home?

  • Please force to be a number with a $ sign as above

  • If the answer is 'YES' to this question please remove the question - What is your monthly rent

  • Please force all cells that require a number answer

  • For this section of the question, please force a number for each cell and add a '%' sign at the end of the answer. Please remove the + sign at the side as it is not required to add additional rows for this.

  • Question - Do you have any investment properties?

  • If the answer is 'NO' please remove this section on investment debt

  • If the answer is yes please fix the question ' What is the current rent per week' it should be 'Please provide details of your investment properties'

Again force numbers for answers… the third question "What is your current rent" please make it "What is your current weekly rent?'

Again please force a number in the % cell and add the % sign at the end

  • Questions below:

  • Again force a number in each cell that requires a number:

  • The above Value of your spouse/partners superannuation fund should only come up if they answer 'Yes' to the spouse/partner question

  • Questions - Do you have children?

  • The question about living expenses shouldn't be related to if the client has children or not, it should be a separate question that is always asked.

  • Please force the correct format on each answer eg date of birth is a date and education cost is a number.

  • For the attachments line

  • Please change the title of this from 'Attachments' to 'Please attach any superannuation statements or insurance schedules to be included in the analysis'

Wilton Wong

Managing Director

Heath, hi

Thanks for the initial setup of the insurance analysis.

Playing with the calculator I did find quite a few questions missing from the excel I provided and some changes from my end so it feels and flows better.

Can we look at changing the following:

  1. Can we make the boxes grey like the insurance calculator.

  2. Can we change the title from 'Insurance Questions' to 'Insurance Analysis'

  3. Add in questions after title:

    1. Your name

  1. For spouse if they answer 'yes' can we make the following changes:

    1. Change to 'Spouse/Partner' for all reference to spouse

    2. In the income box can we force it to be a number like the insurance calculator

  1. Do you own your own home?

    1. If the answer is 'no' please ask the rent questions - do not ask the rent question if the answer is yes

    2. All the questions which require a number again can we force it to be a number

    3. For these three questions:

<image001.png>

Can we structure it like the investment property question so replace 'Properties' with the question 'What percentage of your home mortgage would you want repaid in the event of:'

And then change the three boxes titles to 'Death', 'Total Permanent Disablement', 'Trauma' and the answer in the box must be a number (which is a percentage)

<image002.jpg>

Do the same for the spouse as well ' What percentage of your home mortgage would you want repaid in the event of for your Spouse/Partner:

  1. For the investment properties question

    1. please change the title of the box to

What is the current rent per week?

<image002.jpg>

    1. for the percentage of repayment question can you structure it the same way as above, just like the home mortgage debt.

<image003.png>

Also if the person has a spouse please ask the same question for the spouse. If no spouse then don't ask the question

  1. Value of any cash at bank, again any question which requires a number can we force the number to be entered like the insurance calculator

  2. For 'Value of any other assets you wish to include?' please change this to 'Value of any assets you wish to include in the insurance analysis'

  3. Do you smoke question, if the person answers no they still need to ask the question if the spouse smokes if that is applicable

  4. For the last two questions on the assistance with a Nanny, if they answer yes can you pop up a text box so they can write some detail.

Put the title as 'please provide detail of the assistance you require'

  1. The children questions are missing

  2. Can you add a question 'Do you have any existing insurance?', if the answer is yes open a text box to provide details

  3. What is your current monthly living expenses question is missing

  4. Heath is there a way to add attachments?

Thanks

Wilton
